The paper presents a new corpus for named entity recognition in the science exam domain, which is a natural language processing task falling under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of a BERT-based model for multi-label classification, which is a popular technique in machine learning and deep learning (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DL). Additionally, the paper involves a data-driven analysis of science exam questions, which could potentially fall under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR).
